  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to test the hypothesis of whether contrast enhanced Magnetic
      Resonance Imaging can be used to predict improvement of the wall motion in regions of the
      heart with abnormal movement following bypass surgery or percutaneous angioplasty in various
      institutions across three continents.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
